metadata.name: Top of Mountains #22
metadata.description:
Isn't the view beautiful on top of the mountains?

Sky, clouds, and mountains are generated with random dots, lines and shapes.
Made with p5.js.

Features:
1. Time: Day/Sunset/Night
2. Clouds: Yes/None
3. Light Source: Left/Right

Keys:
s: save the image as PNG
2: save the image in medium resolution 2000x2000
4: save the image in high resolution 4000x4000

When saving the image in medium/high resolutions, please note that it takes several seconds to redraw before the image is downloaded.

metadata.name: Labyrinth #137
metadata.description:
The beginning of life is an incessant dream, a kaleidoscope of surprising discoveries, a colorful labyrinth in which you are enclosed by indefinitely high walls or a void, which you have to pass on your own. The person who may later become a guide through the labyrinth is still hiding behind some wall, past another turn. The main goal is to find him. If you succeed...


But you will succeed.


© Victoria Crux, 2022

metadata.name: Kinetograms #228
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.name: Zephyr #394
metadata.description:
The name Zephyr traces back to Zephyrus, the Greek god of the west wind, and refers to any light breeze. The flowing particles get pushed around by a zephyr, creating interesting and organic patterns.

Live Mode Controls:

- Default is 2000x2000 pixel canvas. Press “1” for 1000x1000px canvas, “3” for 3000x3000px, “4” for 4000x4000px
- Press 'p' to save a png of the canvas.

Created using p5.js

Licensed under CC BY-NC 4.0

metadata.name: BULLET #127
Mustachioed #121
metadata.description:
Who has the chance to have a weird mustache on his face?
Art, personality, politics, religion, power or any other factor has made some mustache models dependent on individuals and takes its name from its first or most famous owner.
Mustachioed is a historical research that aims to link the history of the mustache to the digital world.
Each piece of mustachioed is a ticket to enter this unique world where different samples of mustaches are collected.
Who has the chance to register an outstanding mustache to their names?
We must wait and see.
This research will continue!

Collection of unique men with weird mustaches. Including 13 traits and 473 Attributes.
